The paper presents a novel visualization algorithm for conformally parameterizing and deforming a selected local region-of-interest (ROI) on an arbitrary surface for biomedical visualization. This involves resolving occlusions locally while preserving the overall geometric context. The paper also presents three challenging use cases, which are related to computer graphics (cs.GR), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and biomedical imaging (cs.BI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CG, and cs.BI, in that order.
